OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,FThe annual UK temperature was 1.66C
OL,8,Fhigher than the average between 1961
OL,9,Fand 1990.
OL,11,FThe report flagged two key trends. The
OL,12,Fnumber of 'hot' days (28C or above)
OL,13,Fand 'extremely wet' days are both
OL,14,Fincreasing.
OL,16,FBetween 1961 and 1990, London and
OL,17,FHampshire were the only places to
OL,18,Faverage six or more days over 28C.
