OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,F"By 2050, a year like 2023 would be
OL,8,Ffairly average, and by the end of the
OL,9,Fcentury, it is likely to be a very
OL,10,Fcool year," lead author and Met Office
OL,11,Fclimate scientist Mike Kendon said.
OL,13,F"These projections going forward show
OL,14,Fus just how dramatically we expect our
OL,15,Fclimate to change in the future."
OL,17,FFor context, last year's weather was
OL,18,Fmade more extreme by the natural ocean
OL,19,Fwarming phenomenon called El Nino -
OL,20,Fbut the trends are clear.
